Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 04-17-18.
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three (3) years, six (6) months.    Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision on each count concurrent.  Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.    Conditions of extended supervision are: 
1) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Defendant is entitled to 378 days sentence credit.   
Minutes.

NO CONTEST pleas entered to counts 1 and 2, two counts deliver THC.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 3, 4 and 5.  Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination;
3) acquire a diploma or HSED;
4) AODA assessment;
5) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) pay court costs of $873.00;
7) Submit to DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The Court orders expungement under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.
Minutes.
